185
00:07:49,440 --> 00:07:50,440
Overall.
总体。

186
00:07:50,440 --> 00:07:53,520
So this is the same as saying on the whole.
这和说“整体上”是一样的。

187
00:07:53,520 --> 00:07:54,520
Right.
对。

188
00:07:54,520 --> 00:07:56,000
So it's a big picture, how you would say.
所以它是大局观，可以这么说。

189
00:07:56,000 --> 00:07:57,240
Yeah, in general.
是的，总的来说。

190
00:07:57,240 --> 00:07:58,280
In general.
总的来说。

191
00:07:58,280 --> 00:08:00,320
So his overall performance is good.
所以他的总体表现不错。

192
00:08:00,320 --> 00:08:01,880
It means in general.
意思是总的来说。

193
00:08:01,880 --> 00:08:03,360
His performance is good.
他的表现不错。

194
00:08:03,360 --> 00:08:04,360
Perfect.
完美。

195
00:08:04,360 --> 00:08:08,240
And our last phrase is very interesting because we can mix it up a little bit.
最后一个短语很有趣，因为我们可以稍微变通一下。

196
00:08:08,240 --> 00:08:09,240
Yep.
嗯。

197
00:08:09,240 --> 00:08:10,240
Perfectly good.
非常好。

198
00:08:10,240 --> 00:08:11,240
Perfectly good.
非常好。

199
00:08:11,240 --> 00:08:12,240
Perfectly good.
非常好。

200
00:08:12,240 --> 00:08:14,120
Perfectly good.
非常好。

201
00:08:14,120 --> 00:08:18,720
So this is an interesting phrase because you can describe different objects in this way.
这是一个有趣的短语，因为你可以用这种方式描述不同的物体。

202
00:08:18,720 --> 00:08:19,720
Yeah.
是的。

203
00:08:19,720 --> 00:08:21,240
A perfectly good reason.
一个完全合理的理由。

204
00:08:21,240 --> 00:08:23,080
A perfectly good car.
一辆完好的车。

205
00:08:23,080 --> 00:08:24,720
A perfectly good computer.
一台完好的电脑。

206
00:08:24,720 --> 00:08:27,040
So by the sounds of it, it's kind of like justifying.
听起来像是在辩解。

207
00:08:27,040 --> 00:08:28,040
Yeah.
是的。

208
00:08:28,040 --> 00:08:29,680
It's saying there's no problem with it.
意思是它没有问题。

209
00:08:29,680 --> 00:08:30,680
There's no problem with it.
它没有问题。

210
00:08:30,680 --> 00:08:34,040
Why would you throw it away if it's a perfectly good computer?
如果它是一台完好的电脑，你为什么要扔掉它？

211
00:08:34,040 --> 00:08:35,040
Exactly.
没错。

212
00:08:35,040 --> 00:08:36,040
Okay.
好的。

213
00:08:36,040 --> 00:08:37,040
Perfectly good.
完好的。

214
00:08:37,040 --> 00:08:38,040
Okay.
好的。

215
00:08:38,040 --> 00:08:42,240
So now we can listen to our dialogue a third time at a normal speed and now we're ready
现在我们可以以正常速度第三次听对话，我们已经准备好

216
00:08:42,240 --> 00:08:45,240
to understand everything.
理解所有内容了。

217
00:08:45,240 --> 00:08:58,200
So, Lauren, I just wanted to talk to you quickly about our new customer support representative,
劳伦，我想和你简单谈谈我们的新客服代表，

218
00:08:58,200 --> 00:08:59,200
Jason Huntley.
杰森·亨特利。

219
00:08:59,200 --> 00:09:00,200
Sure.
当然。

220
00:09:00,200 --> 00:09:01,200
What's up?
怎么了？

221
00:09:01,200 --> 00:09:05,960
Basically, I've got a few concerns about him and the bottom line is I don't think he's
基本上，我对他有些担忧，归根结底，我认为他不太

222
00:09:05,960 --> 00:09:07,720
a good fit for our company.
适合我们公司。

223
00:09:07,720 --> 00:09:08,720
Okay.
好吧。

224
00:09:08,720 --> 00:09:09,720
What makes you say that?
你为什么这么说？

225
00:09:09,720 --> 00:09:13,280
I thought you were pleased with his overall performance.
我以为你对他的整体表现很满意。

226
00:09:13,280 --> 00:09:16,560
Didn't you just tell me last week how impressed you were with his attitude?
你上周不是还告诉我你对他的态度印象深刻吗？

227
00:09:16,560 --> 00:09:17,560
Yeah.
是的。

228
00:09:17,560 --> 00:09:21,240
His attitude is great, but he's really unreliable.
他的态度很好，但他真的很不可靠。

229
00:09:21,240 --> 00:09:25,720
Sometimes he's really productive, but then other times, take last Tuesday for instance,
有时他效率很高，但其他时候，比如上周二，

230
00:09:25,720 --> 00:09:28,680
he was 45 minutes late for our morning meeting.
他早会迟到了45分钟。

231
00:09:28,680 --> 00:09:31,240
Well, I'm sure he had a perfectly good reason.
嗯，我肯定他有完全合理的理由。

232
00:09:31,240 --> 00:09:32,880
But that's not the only thing.
但这还不是全部。

233
00:09:32,880 --> 00:09:36,120
You know, he really doesn't have the best work ethic.
你知道，他的职业道德真的不太好。

234
00:09:36,120 --> 00:09:41,480
I'm constantly catching him on MSN and Facebook when he should be talking to clients.
我经常发现他在应该和客户通话的时候上MSN和Facebook。

235
00:09:41,480 --> 00:09:43,480
Yeah, but come on, Jeff.
是啊，但拜托，杰夫。

236
00:09:43,480 --> 00:09:45,560
As if you don't check Facebook at work.
好像你上班时不查Facebook似的。

237
00:09:45,560 --> 00:09:47,520
Look, you hired this guy.
听着，是你雇了这个人。

238
00:09:47,520 --> 00:09:50,360
We've invested a lot of time and money in his training.
我们在他的培训上投入了大量时间和金钱。

239
00:09:50,360 --> 00:09:52,240
So now it's up to you to coach him.
所以现在由你来指导他。

240
00:09:52,240 --> 00:09:58,800
Make it work, Jeff.
想办法搞定，杰夫。

241
00:09:58,800 --> 00:09:59,880
Make it work, Jeff.
搞定它，杰夫。

242
00:09:59,880 --> 00:10:01,360
You would say that, wouldn't you?
你肯定会这么说，不是吗？

243
00:10:01,360 --> 00:10:02,360
He is your cousin.
他是你表弟。

244
00:10:02,360 --> 00:10:03,360
What a jerk.
真是个混蛋。

245
00:10:03,360 --> 00:10:07,480
Making me hire your stupid, useless cousin.
逼我雇你那愚蠢又没用的表弟。

246
00:10:07,480 --> 00:10:08,480
Okay.
好吧。

247
00:10:08,480 --> 00:10:12,360
I hope everyone enjoyed our lesson today.
希望大家喜欢今天的课程。

248
